long_desc.thetext: The RecursiveCheckBoxTree is broken as well
Both demos (appear to be broken since 0.7.3) are being moved from example section to test section of demobrowser (TreeVirtual being labeled an experimental feature in 0.7.x).

Although I don't like the looks of the checkboxes there, I don't see from the screenshot what's broken about it. What am I missing?
Derrell
The tree icons and the labels overlay each other.
Hmm, a lot of assignees seem to be missing from bugzilla lately. Re-assigned to Derrell, please have a look.

Adding a checkbox near the tree icon works in 0.8 (see demo "Tree Columns").
I am unable to build 0.7 from latest svn due to script errors (isn't one just supposed to be able to type "make source" from the frontend/application/demobrowser directory?), so I can't test it there. I had applied a patch from Helder Magalhaes on 14 Sep 2008 that he had requested to make CheckBoxTree usable again after it had not been working for some very long time. This bug may be related to that.
I recall some bug that got fixed someplace during the past 1/2 year or so, where image resizing was not working correctly. I suspect a related issue here, based on the crammed-together checkbox and icon, and the appearance that both of those images are too large for their alloted space.
Derrell
unlikely to be fixed for 0.8.3, moved to 0.9
mass renaming of 0.9 target to 1.0 (for issues with status "NEW")
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
